(
  'Understanding WIOA Funding: Your Path to Free Career Training',
  'understanding-wioa-funding',
  'The Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act (WIOA) provides funding for career training at no cost to eligible individuals. Learn how to qualify and apply.',
  E'# Understanding WIOA Funding: Your Path to Free Career Training\n\nThe Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act (WIOA) is a federal program that provides funding for career training and education. If you''re looking to change careers or gain new skills, WIOA funding could cover 100% of your training costs.\n\n## Who Qualifies for WIOA?\n\nWIOA funding is available to individuals who meet specific eligibility criteria:\n\n- Adults (18+) who are unemployed or underemployed\n- Dislocated workers who lost their jobs due to layoffs or business closures\n- Youth (16-24) who face barriers to employment\n- Veterans transitioning to civilian careers\n- Individuals receiving public assistance\n\n## What Does WIOA Cover?\n\nWIOA funding can cover:\n\n- Tuition and training costs\n- Books and supplies\n- Certification exam fees\n- Transportation assistance\n- Childcare support (in some cases)\n- Tools and equipment needed for training\n\n## How to Apply\n\n1. **Visit Your Local WorkOne Center**: Find your nearest center at in.gov/dwd/workone-centers\n2. **Complete an Assessment**: Staff will evaluate your eligibility and career goals\n3. **Develop a Training Plan**: Work with a career advisor to choose an approved training program\n4. **Get Approved**: Once approved, your training costs are covered\n\n## Approved Training Programs\n\nElevate for Humanity offers WIOA-approved programs in:\n\n- HVAC Technician Training\n- Certified Nursing Assistant (CNA)\n- Building Maintenance Technology\n- Barber Apprenticeship\n- And more\n\nAll programs are listed on Indiana''s Eligible Training Provider List (ETPL).\n\n## Next Steps\n\nReady to start your career training journey? Contact your local WorkOne center or apply directly through Indiana Career Connect at indianacareerconnect.com.\n\nQuestions? Email us at info@elevateforhumanity.org or call (317) 314-3757.',
  'Resource',
  'published',
  NOW() - INTERVAL '5 days',
  'Elevate for Humanity',
  '/images/blog/wioa-funding.jpg',
  ARRAY['WIOA', 'Funding', 'Career Training', 'Workforce Development']
),
(
  'The Growing Demand for HVAC Technicians in Indiana',
  'hvac-technician-demand-indiana',
  'Indiana faces a critical shortage of skilled HVAC technicians. Learn about career opportunities, salary expectations, and how to enter this in-demand field.',
  E'# The Growing Demand for HVAC Technicians in Indiana\n\nIndiana is experiencing a significant shortage of skilled HVAC technicians, creating excellent career opportunities for those entering the field.\n\n## Industry Growth\n\nAccording to the Bureau of Labor Statistics:\n\n- HVAC jobs are projected to grow 5% nationally through 2032\n- Indiana specifically needs 1,200+ new HVAC technicians annually\n- Retirement of current technicians is creating additional openings\n\n## Salary and Benefits\n\n**Entry-Level HVAC Technicians in Indiana:**\n- Starting salary: $35,000 - $45,000\n- Experienced technicians: $50,000 - $70,000+\n- Master technicians: $75,000 - $90,000+\n\n**Benefits typically include:**\n- Health insurance\n- Retirement plans\n- Tool allowances\n- Company vehicle\n- Overtime opportunities\n- Continuing education\n\n## Why HVAC?\n\n**Job Security**: Every home, business, and facility needs HVAC services year-round.\n\n**Career Growth**: Start as a technician, advance to lead tech, supervisor, or start your own business.\n\n**Hands-On Work**: If you enjoy problem-solving and working with your hands, HVAC offers daily variety.\n\n**Quick Training**: Most programs take 12-20 weeks, not years.\n\n## Training Requirements\n\n1. **Technical Training**: Complete an HVAC program (12-20 weeks)\n2. **EPA Certification**: Required to handle refrigerants\n3. **Apprenticeship**: Many start as apprentices while learning\n4. **Licensing**: Indiana requires HVAC contractor license for business owners\n\n## Get Started\n\nElevate for Humanity offers WIOA-approved HVAC training in Indianapolis. Our program includes:\n\n- Hands-on lab work with real equipment\n- EPA certification preparation\n- Job placement assistance\n- Connections to local HVAC employers\n\nFunding available through WIOA for eligible individuals.\n\nLearn more: elevateforhumanity.org/programs/hvac-technician',
  'Career Insights',
  'published',
  NOW() - INTERVAL '10 days',
  'Elevate for Humanity',
  '/images/blog/hvac-career.jpg',
  ARRAY['HVAC', 'Career', 'Indiana', 'Skilled Trades']
),
(
  'Registered Apprenticeships: Earn While You Learn',
  'registered-apprenticeships-earn-while-learn',
  'Registered apprenticeships combine on-the-job training with classroom instruction, allowing you to earn a paycheck while gaining skills and credentials.',
  E'# Registered Apprenticeships: Earn While You Learn\n\nRegistered apprenticeships offer a proven pathway to skilled careers without student debt. You earn a wage from day one while learning a trade.\n\n## What is a Registered Apprenticeship?\n\nA Registered Apprenticeship is a U.S. Department of Labor-approved training program that combines:\n\n- **On-the-Job Training**: Work with experienced mentors in real work environments\n- **Related Instruction**: Classroom learning to support hands-on skills\n- **Progressive Wages**: Earn more as your skills increase\n- **Industry Credentials**: Receive nationally recognized certifications\n\n## Benefits of Apprenticeship\n\n**Financial:**\n- Get paid while you train (no tuition debt)\n- Wages increase as skills develop\n- Many employers offer benefits (health insurance, retirement)\n\n**Career:**\n- Gain real work experience\n- Build professional network\n- Earn industry-recognized credentials\n- Higher lifetime earnings than non-apprentices\n\n**Education:**\n- Structured learning path\n- Mentorship from experienced professionals\n- Stackable credentials\n\n## Available Apprenticeships\n\nElevate for Humanity offers DOL-registered apprenticeships in:\n\n### Barber Apprenticeship\n- Duration: 2,000 hours (1-2 years)\n- Earn while learning in licensed barbershops\n- Pathway to state licensure\n- Build client portfolio\n\n### Building Maintenance Technician\n- Duration: 2-3 years\n- Learn electrical, plumbing, HVAC basics\n- Work in facilities, housing authorities, schools\n- Stable, year-round employment\n\n### HVAC Technician\n- Duration: 3-4 years\n- Starting wage: $15-$25/hour\n- EPA certification included\n- High demand, excellent career growth\n\n## How to Apply\n\n1. **Check Eligibility**: Most programs require age 18+, high school diploma/GED\n2. **Submit Application**: Apply through Indiana Career Connect\n3. **Interview**: Meet with program coordinators\n4. **Get Matched**: We connect you with employer sponsors\n5. **Start Earning**: Begin your apprenticeship with a paycheck\n\n## Funding Support\n\nMany apprenticeships qualify for:\n- WIOA funding for related instruction\n- Employer-sponsored training\n- On-the-job training (OJT) grants\n\n## Success Stories\n\nOur apprentices have gone on to:\n- Open their own barbershops\n- Become lead HVAC technicians\n- Advance to facilities management roles\n- Earn $50,000+ annually within 3-5 years\n\n## Ready to Start?\n\nExplore our registered apprenticeship programs:\n- Visit: elevateforhumanity.org/apprenticeships\n- Call: (317) 314-3757\n- Email: info@elevateforhumanity.org\n\nNo student debt. Real skills. Real paycheck. Real career.',
  'Programs',
  'published',
  NOW() - INTERVAL '15 days',
  'Elevate for Humanity',
  '/images/blog/apprenticeships.jpg',
  ARRAY['Apprenticeship', 'Career Training', 'DOL', 'Skilled Trades']
),
(
  'CNA Training: Your Entry Point to Healthcare Careers',
  'cna-training-healthcare-entry',
  'Certified Nursing Assistant (CNA) training provides a fast entry into healthcare with strong job security and opportunities for advancement.',
  E'# CNA Training: Your Entry Point to Healthcare Careers\n\nBecoming a Certified Nursing Assistant (CNA) is one of the fastest ways to enter the healthcare field. Training takes just 4-8 weeks, and CNAs are in high demand across Indiana.\n\n## What Does a CNA Do?\n\nCNAs provide direct patient care in hospitals, nursing homes, assisted living facilities, and home health settings:\n\n- Monitor vital signs (blood pressure, temperature, pulse)\n- Assist with daily activities (bathing, dressing, eating)\n- Help patients with mobility and transfers\n- Document patient information\n- Provide emotional support to patients and families\n\n## Why Choose CNA?\n\n**Fast Training**: Most programs are 4-8 weeks, not years\n\n**High Demand**: Healthcare facilities constantly need CNAs\n\n**Job Security**: Healthcare is recession-resistant\n\n**Career Ladder**: CNA is a stepping stone to LPN, RN, or other healthcare roles\n\n**Meaningful Work**: Make a real difference in people''s lives daily\n\n## Salary and Employment\n\n**Indiana CNA Wages:**\n- Entry-level: $28,000 - $32,000/year\n- Experienced: $35,000 - $40,000/year\n- Specialized settings: $40,000 - $45,000/year\n\n**Work Settings:**\n- Hospitals\n- Nursing homes/Long-term care\n- Assisted living facilities\n- Home health agencies\n- Rehabilitation centers\n- Hospice care\n\n## Training Requirements\n\n**Indiana CNA Requirements:**\n1. Complete state-approved CNA training program (75+ hours)\n2. Pass state competency exam (written + skills)\n3. Background check\n4. Health screening and immunizations\n\n**Training Includes:**\n- Classroom instruction\n- Skills lab practice\n- Clinical experience in healthcare facilities\n\n## Funding Options\n\nCNA training is often fully funded through:\n- WIOA workforce funding\n- Hospital and nursing home sponsorships\n- Healthcare workforce initiatives\n- Scholarships\n\n## Career Advancement\n\nMany CNAs advance to:\n- **Licensed Practical Nurse (LPN)**: 1 year additional training\n- **Registered Nurse (RN)**: 2-4 years additional education\n- **Medical Assistant**: Lateral move with additional skills\n- **Specialized CNA**: Dialysis, hospice, pediatrics\n\n## Next Steps\n\nElevate for Humanity partners with state-approved CNA training providers. We help you:\n\n1. Find approved training programs\n2. Apply for funding (WIOA, scholarships)\n3. Navigate the application process\n4. Connect with hiring healthcare facilities\n\n**Get Started:**\n- Apply: indianacareerconnect.com\n- Questions: info@elevateforhumanity.org\n- Phone: (317) 314-3757\n\nStart your healthcare career in weeks, not years.',
  'Career Insights',
  'published',
  NOW() - INTERVAL '20 days',
  'Elevate for Humanity',
  '/images/blog/cna-training.jpg',
  ARRAY['CNA', 'Healthcare', 'Career Training', 'Nursing']
),
(
  'How to Choose the Right Career Training Program',
  'choose-right-career-training-program',
  'Selecting the right training program is crucial for your career success. Learn what to look for and questions to ask before enrolling.',
  E'# How to Choose the Right Career Training Program\n\nChoosing the right career training program is one of the most important decisions you''ll make. Here''s how to evaluate your options and make an informed choice.\n\n## Key Factors to Consider\n\n### 1. Accreditation and Approval\n\n**Look for:**\n- State approval (Indiana Commission for Higher Education)\n- Industry-recognized accreditation\n- Listed on Indiana''s Eligible Training Provider List (ETPL)\n- DOL-registered apprenticeships (if applicable)\n\n**Why it matters**: Approved programs qualify for funding and are recognized by employers.\n\n### 2. Job Placement Rates\n\n**Ask:**\n- What percentage of graduates find employment?\n- How long does it take graduates to find jobs?\n- What is the average starting salary?\n- Do you provide job placement assistance?\n\n**Red flags**: Programs that won''t share placement data or have rates below 70%.\n\n### 3. Curriculum and Hands-On Training\n\n**Evaluate:**\n- Balance of classroom vs. hands-on training\n- Access to real equipment and tools\n- Clinical or externship opportunities\n- Industry-current curriculum\n\n**Best practice**: Programs should include significant hands-on practice, not just lectures.\n\n### 4. Instructor Qualifications\n\n**Check:**\n- Do instructors have real industry experience?\n- Are they currently certified in their field?\n- What is the student-to-instructor ratio?\n\n**Ideal**: Instructors who actively work in the field bring current knowledge.\n\n### 5. Cost and Funding Options\n\n**Compare:**\n- Total program cost (tuition, fees, books, supplies)\n- Available funding (WIOA, scholarships, payment plans)\n- Hidden costs (uniforms, certification exams, tools)\n\n**Important**: Many quality programs are fully funded through WIOA for eligible individuals.\n\n### 6. Schedule Flexibility\n\n**Consider:**\n- Full-time vs. part-time options\n- Day, evening, or weekend classes\n- Program length\n- Start dates\n\n**Your needs**: Choose a schedule that fits your life circumstances.\n\n### 7. Support Services\n\n**Available support:**\n- Career counseling\n- Resume and interview preparation\n- Childcare assistance\n- Transportation help\n- Tutoring or academic support\n\n**Success factor**: Strong support services increase completion rates.\n\n## Questions to Ask\n\nBefore enrolling, ask:\n\n1. Is this program approved for WIOA funding?\n2. What credentials will I earn upon completion?\n3. What is your job placement rate?\n4. Can I speak with recent graduates?\n5. What employers hire your graduates?\n6. What happens if I need to pause my training?\n7. Do you offer job placement assistance?\n8. What is included in the tuition cost?\n\n## Warning Signs\n\n**Avoid programs that:**\n- Pressure you to enroll immediately\n- Won''t provide placement data\n- Require large upfront payments\n- Make unrealistic salary promises\n- Aren''t approved for workforce funding\n- Have poor online reviews from students\n\n## Elevate for Humanity Programs\n\nAll our programs feature:\n\n✅ WIOA-approved (on Indiana''s ETPL)\n✅ Industry-recognized credentials\n✅ Hands-on training with real equipment\n✅ Job placement assistance\n✅ Experienced instructors\n✅ Flexible scheduling options\n✅ Comprehensive support services\n\n## Make Your Decision\n\n1. **Research**: Compare 2-3 programs in your field\n2. **Visit**: Tour facilities and meet instructors\n3. **Talk to Students**: Get honest feedback\n4. **Check Funding**: Apply for WIOA or other funding\n5. **Enroll**: Choose the program that best fits your goals\n\n**Need Help Deciding?**\n\nContact us for guidance:\n- Email: info@elevateforhumanity.org\n- Phone: (317) 314-3757\n- Visit: elevateforhumanity.org/programs\n\nYour career success starts with the right training choice.',
  'Resource',
  'published',
  NOW() - INTERVAL '25 days',
  'Elevate for Humanity',
  '/images/blog/choose-program.jpg',
  ARRAY['Career Planning', 'Training', 'Education', 'Workforce Development']
);

-- Update blog_posts table to ensure all required columns exist
ALTER TABLE blog_posts ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS author_name TEXT DEFAULT 'Elevate for Humanity';
ALTER TABLE blog_posts ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS featured_image TEXT;
ALTER TABLE blog_posts ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS tags TEXT[];
ALTER TABLE blog_posts ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS views INTEGER DEFAULT 0;
ALTER TABLE blog_posts ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS reading_time INTEGER;

-- Calculate reading time for existing posts (average 200 words per minute)
UPDATE blog_posts 
SET reading_time = GREATEST(1, LENGTH(content) / 1000)
WHERE reading_time IS NULL;

COMMENT ON TABLE blog_posts IS 'Real blog posts about workforce development, career training, and program information';
